                <div class="FAQ" onclick="toggle('faq1')">
                    1. What is PANDA?
                    <div id="faq1" class="ANS">
                        PANDA is the Pathway and Annotation visualization tool.
                        It allows users to get a high level overview of annotations and data together in the context of
                        intuitive biological pathways.
                        PANDA can accept any tab-delimited text file as input, and an icon specified by the user.
                        The only requirements are that the first column in the text file must correspond to an HGNC
                        approved gene symbol and that the first line (which represents the headers) starts with a "#".

                        <br><br>
                        As an example use case, imagine the following three source scenario. An investigator loads copy
                        number, gene expression, and drug targets to see if there are any relationships.
                        Because each icon is different from the three sources, one can quickly see whether copy number
                        and gene expression corresponds to the same gene.
                        The user can then hover over each icon to see if the fold changes are in the appropriate
                        direction and p-values are significant (if such data is provided).
                        If both are showing signs for activation, then the user can quickly search available drugs that
                        inhibit that gene or others downstream.
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="FAQ" onclick="toggle('faq2')">
                    2. Can I use Entrez Gene IDs instead of HGNC Symbols?
                    <div id="faq2" class="ANS">Unfortunately, PANDA does not support other IDs as inputs.
                        However, if a user wants to keep Entrez IDs as something that can be seen, they can upload any
                        tab-delimited file with Entrez IDs as one of the other columns - as long as
                        the first column is the HGNC Gene Symbol.
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="FAQ" onclick="toggle('faq3')">
                    3. KEGG and BioCarta are nice, but they don't have my pathway of interest. How can I use my pathway
                    with PANDA?
                    <div id="faq3" class="ANS">To use your own pathways as sources, they must be constructed using
                        <a href="http://www.cytoscape.org/" target="_blank">Cytoscape</a>.
                        When you've created the pathways you're interestd in, just export your network as an XGMML file
                        <strong>AND</strong> as a PNG file -(both available options in Cytoscape).
                        Once you have your two input files, sign in to PANDA. From the menu, select
                        <em>Functions=>Upload your Pathway</em> and upload your files.
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="FAQ" onclick="toggle('faq4')">
                    4. How and why would I use the Data Sharing function?
                    <div id="faq4" class="ANS">
                        The grouping function allows you to share your annotations with other people in your group,
                        without them having to upload the data themselves.
                        <br><br>To add users to a group, first create a new group under the menu
                        <em>Share=>Create New Group</em>.
                        First, name your group and add a description so you can refer to it later.
                        You can set <em>Visibility</em> to Private (so that only members of your group can see the
                        annotation) or public (anyone using PANDA).
                        By default, annotations are all private. All annotations that are available to you are
                        optionally available to members of your group.
                        Use the checkboxes to select the annotations that you want to share with your group, since some
                        might not be of interest to them.
                        Finally, add the usernames of the members and click <em>Create Group</em>.
                        Members of your group now have access to view your annotations!.
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="FAQ" onclick="toggle('faq5')">
                    5. There are links to pathways on the BioCarta website that I don't see in PANDA. Where did they go?
